Title: The Coffee Shop Mystery
Author: Sample Writer

INT. COFFEE SHOP - DAY

The small coffee shop is bustling with morning customers. SARAH, 30s, enters nervously, clutching a worn envelope.

She scans the room, looking for someone.

SARAH
(to herself)
Where is he?

BARISTA, 20s, calls out from behind the counter.

BARISTA
Next in line, please!

Sarah approaches the counter, still distracted.

SARAH
Just a black coffee, please.

BARISTA
Coming right up.

Sarah takes her coffee and sits at a corner table. She opens the envelope and pulls out an old photograph.

A MAN IN A HAT, 40s, enters and walks directly to Sarah's table.

MAN IN HAT
You have something that belongs to me.

SARAH
(defensive)
I don't know what you're talking about.

MAN IN HAT
The photograph. My father gave it to your mother twenty years ago.

Sarah looks at the photo, then back at the man.

SARAH
How do I know you're telling the truth?

The man sits down across from her.

MAN IN HAT
Because I have the other half.

He pulls out another photograph from his jacket. The two pieces fit together perfectly.

FADE OUT.
